race.comment: BE QUIET (8) progressive mare who launched late when held up briefly in the straight for a sound fourth over 1100m at Canterbury. Will hold a forward position and should prove too slick for these. INOUE (1) tough win two-back at Hawkesbury, before jumping sharply in grade when a respectable sixth to Apex over 1100m in a BM78 at Canterbury. Maps well and the winkers go on. STILL ALICE (9) returned from a let-up when fading quickly with a poor seventh over this track and trip. Drops in weight and should've tightened up further. Keep safe. ZOE SHARK (2) tough mare racing in career best form. Just failed to pick them up with the 58kg when third over 900m at Muswellbrook. Sure to be thereabouts.
